HEADWORD: Manbote
<hw>Man"bote`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>man</ets>
man, vassal + <ets>b⟦omac⟧t</ets> recompense.]</ety> <fld>(Anglo-Saxon
Law)</fld> <def>A sum paid to a lord as a pecuniary compensation for
killing his man (that is, his vassal, servant, or tenant).</def>
<rj><au>Spelman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

